{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_912484", "question": "Mrs. Oaklyn buys handmade rugs at $40 each and sells them at $60 each. If she bought 20 rugs, calculate the profit she will make from selling the rugs.\nThoughts? Step-by-step reasoning:", "answer": "Step 1: Calculate the cost of the rugs Mrs. Oaklyn bought.\nTo find the cost of the 20 rugs, we will multiply the cost per rug ($40) by the number of rugs (20).\nCost = $40 * 20 = $800\n\nStep 2: Calculate the revenue from selling the rugs.\nTo find the revenue, we will multiply the selling price per rug ($60) by the number of rugs (20).\nRevenue = $60 * 20 = $1200\n\nStep 3: Calculate the profit.\nTo find the profit, we will subtract the cost from the revenue.\nProfit = Revenue - Cost\nProfit = $1200 - $800 = $400\n\nMrs. Oaklyn will make a profit of $400 from selling the 20 rugs."}
{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_442194", "question": "List the five major classes of medications used to treat hypertension and provide a brief description of their mechanism of action.", "answer": "1. Angiotensin-converting enzyme (ACE) inhibitors: They work by blocking the production of angiotensin II, a hormone that constricts blood vessels and increases blood pressure.\n2. Angiotensin II receptor blockers (ARBs): They block the action of angiotensin II by preventing it from binding to its receptor, causing blood vessels to relax and blood pressure to reduce.\n3. Calcium channel blockers: These medications inhibit the entry of calcium into the cells of the heart and blood vessels, which leads to the relaxation of blood vessels and a reduction in blood pressure.\n4. Diuretics: They help the kidneys remove excess salt and water from the body, thereby reducing blood volume and lowering blood pressure.\n5. Beta-blockers: They work by reducing the heart rate and the force of heart contractions, which lowers blood pressure."}
