oyee_id,]\n  \n  # Check if last update was more than 6 months ago\n  last_update <- employee_record$last_update\n  if (as.numeric(Sys.Date() - last_update, \"days\") > 180) {\n    return(TRUE)\n  }\n  \n  # Check if salary has changed by more than 10%\n  current_salary <- employee_record$salary\n  last_salary <- employee_record$last_salary\n  if (abs(current_salary - last_salary) / last_salary > 0.1) {\n    return(TRUE)\n  }\n  \n  # Check if work location has changed\n  current_location <- employee_record$work_location\n  last_location <- employee_record$last_location\n  if (current_location != last_location) {\n    return(TRUE)\n  }\n  \n  # No update needed\n  return(FALSE)\n}\n\n# Example usage\nemployee_data$last_salary <- employee_data$salary\nemployee_data$last_location <- employee_data$work_location\n\nemployee_data[needs_update(1, employee_data),]$last_update <- as.Date(\"2020-01-01\")\nemployee_data[needs_update(2, employee_data),]$last_update <- as.Date(\"2021-03-15\")\nemployee_data[needs_update(3, employee_data),]$last_update <- as.Date(\"2021-06-30\")\nemployee_data[needs_update(4, employee_data),]$last_update <- as.Date(\"2021-08-01\")\n````", "answer": "To modify the given R code to also check if an employee's job title has changed since the last update, we can add a new column to the employee data frame for the job title, and initialize it to \"Software Engineer\" for all employees. Then, we can modify the `needs_update` function to include an additional check for job title change. If the job title has changed, we want to set the last update date to today's date for that employee.\n\nHere's the modified code:\n\n```R\n# Create employee data frame\nemployee_data <- data.frame(\n  employee_id = c(1, 2, 3, 4),\n  employee_name = c(\"Alice\", \"Bob\", \"Charlie\", \"Dave\"),\n  salary = c(50000, 60000, 55000, 65000),\n  work_location = c(\"New York\", \"Boston\", \"Chicago\", \"San Francisco\"),\n  job_title = rep(\"Software Engineer\", 4) # add job ti