{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_270966", "question": "I have a table containing user information and I need to retrieve all the unique usernames from it. How can I write an SQL query to accomplish this? And also, I want the results to be sorted in alphabetical order. Can you help me with this?", "answer": "Sure! To retrieve all the unique usernames from your table and sort them alphabetically, you can use the following SQL query:\n\n```sql\nSELECT DISTINCT username FROM users ORDER BY username ASC;\n```\n\nIn this query, `users` refers to the name of your table, and `username` is the column that stores the usernames. The `DISTINCT` keyword ensures that only unique usernames are returned in the result set.\n\nThe `ORDER BY` clause is then used to sort the usernames in alphabetical order. By specifying `ASC` after `username`, the sorting will be done in ascending order. If you want the usernames to be sorted in descending order, you can use `DESC` instead.\n\nBy executing this query, you will retrieve all the unique usernames from the `users` table, with the results sorted alphabetically as per your requirement."}
