{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_465323", "question": "Betty and Dora started making some cupcakes at the same time. Betty makes x cupcakes every hour and Dora makes 8 every hour. If Betty took a two-hour break, what is the difference between the number of cupcakes they made after 5 hours?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 10, what is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "Betty makes x cupcakes every hour, so in 5 hours, she makes 5x cupcakes.\nDora makes 8 cupcakes every hour, so in 5 hours, she makes 5 * 8 = 40 cupcakes.\nHowever, Betty took a two-hour break, so she only made cupcakes for 5 - 2 = 3 hours.\nIn 3 hours, Betty made 3x cupcakes.\nThe difference between the number of cupcakes they made after 5 hours is: 40 - 3x.\nWe are given that the difference is 10, so we can write: 40 - 3x = 10.\nSolving for x, we get: 3x = 30.\nDividing both sides by 3, we get: x = 10.\nThe value of x is 10.\n#### 10\nThe answer is: 10"}
