{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_278802", "question": "I want to create a MySQL database for a hotel. How can I set up tables for the properties, types, and owners?", "answer": "To create a MySQL database for a hotel, you can follow these steps:\n\nFirst, create the database by running the command \"CREATE DATABASE hotel_db;\". This will create a new database named \"hotel_db\".\n\nThen, switch to the newly created database using the command \"USE hotel_db;\". This ensures that all subsequent table creations and operations are performed within the context of the \"hotel_db\" database.\n\nNext, you need to create three tables: \"properties\", \"types\", and \"owners\". \n\nThe \"properties\" table can be created with the following SQL code:\n```\nCREATE TABLE properties (\n ID int NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,\n name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,\n address VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,\n type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL\n);\n```\nThis table has columns for the property ID (auto-incremented integer), name (varchar with a maximum length of 50 characters), address (varchar with a maximum length of 50 characters), and type (varchar with a maximum length of 50 characters).\n\nThe \"types\" table can be created with the following SQL code:\n```\nCREATE TABLE types (\n ID int NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,\n type VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL\n);\n```\nThis table has columns for the type ID (auto-incremented integer) and type (varchar with a maximum length of 50 characters).\n\nThe \"owners\" table can be created with the following SQL code:\n```\nCREATE TABLE owners (\n ID int NOT NULL PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,\n name VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL,\n address VARCHAR(50) NOT NULL\n);\n```\nThis table has columns for the owner ID (auto-incremented integer), name (varchar with a maximum length of 50 characters), and address (varchar with a maximum length of 50 characters).\n\nBy executing these SQL commands, you will have successfully set up the required tables for the hotel database."}
