e extra point)\n- First field goal: 3 points\n- Second field goal: 3 points\n\nChargers: \n- First field goal: 3 points\n- Second field goal: 3 points\n- Third field goal: 3 points\n\nNow we add up the points:\n7 (first Chiefs touchdown) + 7 (second Chiefs touchdown) + 3 (first Chiefs field goal) + 3 (second Chiefs field goal) + 3 (first Chargers field goal) + 3 (second Chargers field goal) + 3 (third Chargers field goal) = 29 points\n\nHowever, the final score mentioned in the description is \"Chiefs the victory, 30-27\". This indicates that there might be a mismatch in the points described in the text. Based on the final score, the total points in the game were:\n\nChiefs: 30 points\nChargers: 27 points\n\nTotal points: 30 (Chiefs) + 27 (Chargers) = 57 points"}
{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_55074", "question": "What is the surface area of a cube if all sides measure 8 cm?", "answer": "The surface area of a cube can be calculated using the formula:\n\nSurface Area = 6 * side^2\n\nIn this case, the side of the cube measures 8 cm. So, we can plug in the value into the formula:\n\nSurface Area = 6 * (8 cm)^2\n\nSurface Area = 6 * 64 cm^2\n\nSurface Area = 384 cm^2\n\nThe surface area of the cube is 384 square centimeters."}
