{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_548357", "question": "Solve -7 = -252*o + 259*o for o.\nSolve this problem.", "answer": "To solve the equation -7 = -252o + 259o for o, we will follow these steps:\n\nStep 1: Combine like terms on the right-hand side of the equation.\n\nThe right-hand side has two terms with the variable o, so we'll combine them:\n\n-252o + 259o = 7o\n\nNow the equation becomes:\n\n-7 = 7o\n\nStep 2: Solve for o.\n\nTo isolate the variable o and find its value, we need to divide both sides of the equation by 7:\n\n-7 / 7 = 7o / 7\n\nThis simplifies to:\n\n-1 = o\n\nSo, the solution to the equation -7 = -252o + 259o is o = -1."}
