{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_5606", "question": "Using SQL, write queries to perform various operations on a database containing tables for Employees, Departments and Salaries. Operations should include joining tables, grouping records, calculating aggregates, filtering and sorting results. PLAINFORMAT", "answer": "-- Query 1: Join Employees and Departments table to get employee details along with their department names\nSELECT E.EmployeeID, E.FirstName, E.LastName, D.DepartmentName \nFROM Employees E \nINNER JOIN Departments D ON E.DepartmentID = D.DepartmentID;\n\n-- Query 2: Get the total salary paid for each department\nSELECT D.DepartmentName, SUM(S.Salary) as TotalSalary \nFROM Salaries S \nINNER JOIN Employees E ON S.EmployeeID = E.EmployeeID \nINNER JOIN Departments D ON E.DepartmentID = D.DepartmentID \nGROUP BY D.DepartmentName;\n\n-- Query 3: Get the average salary of employees in each department\nSELECT D.DepartmentName, AVG(S.Salary) as AverageSalary \nFROM Salaries S \nINNER JOIN Employees E ON S.EmployeeID = E.EmployeeID \nINNER JOIN Departments D ON E.DepartmentID = D.DepartmentID \nGROUP BY D.DepartmentName;\n\n-- Query 4: Get the highest salary from each department\nSELECT D.DepartmentName, MAX(S.Salary) as HighestSalary \nFROM Salaries S \nINNER JOIN Employees E ON S.EmployeeID = E.EmployeeID \nINNER JOIN Departments D ON E.DepartmentID = D.DepartmentID \nGROUP BY D.DepartmentName;\n\n-- Query 5: Get all employees who earn more than the average salary\nSELECT E.EmployeeID, E.FirstName, E.LastName, S.Salary \nFROM Employees E \nINNER JOIN Salaries S ON E.EmployeeID = S.EmployeeID \nWHERE S.Salary > (SELECT AVG(Salary) FROM Salaries);\n\n-- Query 6: Sort employees by their last name in ascending order\nSELECT EmployeeID, FirstName, LastName \nFROM Employees \nORDER BY LastName ASC; \n\n-- Query 7: Filter out employees whose salaries are below a certain threshold\nSELECT E.EmployeeID, E.FirstName, E.LastName, S.Salary \nFROM Employees E \nINNER JOIN Salaries S ON E.EmployeeID = S.EmployeeID \nWHERE S.Salary > 50000;"}
