ut refused to recognize his authority as governor.  This caused an uproar in the garrison, as many supported the governor.  Dimmitt declared martial law and soon alienated most of the local residents.  Over the next few months, the area between Goliad and Refugio descended into civil...", "answer": "The person rumored to be accompanied by $50,000, which the Texians in Matagorda planned to steal, was General Martín Perfecto de Cos. The Texians marched on Presidio La Bahía in Goliad intending to kidnap him and take the rumored accompanying money. However, they were unaware that General Cos had already left for Béxar, as he hastened his departure upon learning that Texian troops had attacked Castañeda at Gonzales."}
