{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_730496", "question": "Solve this math problem\n\nSolve 100 = -51*p - 2 for p.", "answer": "To solve the given math problem, we need to find the value of p in the equation 100 = -51 * p - 2.\n\nStep 1: Isolate the term with p\n\nTo do this, we will first move the constant term to the other side of the equation. In this case, the constant term is -2.\n\nTo move this term to the other side, we will add 2 to both sides of the equation.\n\n100 + 2 = -51 * p - 2 + 2\n\n102 = -51 * p\n\nStep 2: Solve for p\n\nNow that we have isolated the term with p, we can find the value of p by dividing both sides of the equation by -51.\n\n102 / -51 = (-51 * p) / -51\n\np = -2\n\nSo, the value of p in the equation 100 = -51 * p - 2 is -2."}
