m tells the real-life escape story of André Devigny from the Montluc prison during World War II. \n\n6. \"Midnight Express\" (1978): This is based on the true story of Billy Hayes, an American college student who gets caught smuggling drugs out of Turkey and is sentenced to more than 30 years in prison. The film mostly revolves around his multiple attempts to escape. \n\n7. \"Stalag 17\" (1953): Set in a German POW camp during WWII, the story follows a group of American airmen who suspect that one among them is an informant. All the while, they plan an elaborate escape.\n\n8. \"Escape Plan\" (2013): This modern film features Sylvester Stallone as a structural engineer who is wrongfully incarcerated in the maximum-security prison he designed. He then plans an elaborate escape.\n\nAnother variation of the question would be \"Which are the top-rated movies involving prison escapes?\" or \"What are some highly recommended movies about prison breakouts?\" which again share the same sentiment inquiring about notable films in the escape genre."}
