ashes, mass arrests, and several deaths since the announcement of the election results. The official count gave Bongo a second term with 49.8% of the vote, while Ping disputes the results in Bongo's home province of Haut-Ogooue. Turnout varied between provinces, and Ping has called for a recount, which has been resisted by the government."}
