 this case, the term \"normal language\" likely refers to everyday, non-poetic language. In contrast to the first sentence, this statement claims that the optative mood is derived from the imperative mood.\n\nDespite both sentences sharing the theme of expressing hopes or wishes and making a connection between the optative and imperative moods, their respective descriptions and origins of these moods differ. Thus, they cannot be considered exact paraphrases of each other."}
