 rocked by a fresh allegation when Stanton's old friend, \"Big Willie\" McCollister (Tommy Hollis) approaches Henry to tell him that his 17-year-old...", "answer": "Title Suggestion: \"Race for Redemption: The Stanton Chronicles\"\n\nThe movie title \"Race for Redemption: The Stanton Chronicles\" encapsulates the various elements of the plot, as it follows the journey of Jack Stanton and his team trying to win the Democratic Party nomination for President of the United States. The \"Race\" alludes to the intense political competition that the characters navigate throughout the film, while \"Redemption\" is a nod to the various scandals and past indiscretions that Stanton and his team must confront and overcome.\n\nFurthermore, the added subtitle \"The Stanton Chronicles\" emphasizes the central role of the Stanton campaign, as well as the interconnected character arcs that contribute to the movie's overall narrative. By incorporating different aspects of the plot into the title, \"Race for Redemption: The Stanton Chronicles\" offers potential viewers a glimpse into the drama, tension, and excitement that define this intriguing political story."}
