{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_474285", "question": "A cat has nine lives.  A dog has 3 less lives than a cat.  A mouse has x more lives than a dog. A mouse has 13 lives.", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the number of lives a mouse has more than a dog.\nWe know that a mouse has 13 lives and a dog has 3 less lives than a cat.\nLet's break down the information given:\nNumber of lives a cat has: 9\nNumber of lives a dog has: 9 - 3 = 6\nNumber of lives a mouse has: 13\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\nNumber of lives a mouse has = Number of lives a dog has + x\n13 = 6 + x\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\n13 - 6 = x\n7 = x\nThe value of x is 7.\n#### 7\nThe answer is: 7"}
