{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_363712", "question": "I'm trying to extract a plain old `crypto.rsa.PublicKey` from an SSH public key (`x.crypto.ssh.PublicKey`) that I obtained by parsing the `authorized_keys` file. I know that the SSH key is of type `ssh-rsa`. In ssh-land, the key is of (unexported) type `rsaPublicKey`. \n\nBy using either `reflect.Interface()` or `fmt.Sprintf(\"%v\")`, I can get a value that looks like:\n\n```\n&{ 35}\n```\n\nI know from reading the ssh package source that `ssh.rsaPublickey` is the type I want, defined as:\n\n```\ntype rsaPublicKey rsa.PublicKey\n```\n\nSo, the value I obtained is already the desired type. I can even see the fields `N` and `E` using `\"%+v\"`.\n\nThe problem is that I don't know a better way to convince Go that this value is actually an `rsa.PublicKey` than to extract each of the numbers into strings with `fmt.Sscan`, convert them into `big.Int` and `int`, and then use those values as the modulus and exponent to create a new `rsa.PublicKey`. This approach works, but it feels extremely messy. Since the type is unexported, there is probably no direct approach, but surely there must be a better way to access the fields without converting their printable representations back and forth.\n\nThe `ssh.PublicKey` type does have a `Marshal()` function, but that gives me the wire-format representation. If I go down that route, I would have to write my own byte-stream-to-big-Int-to-RSA converter, which doesn't seem like a good solution either. In that case, I might as well parse the `authorized_keys` file myself, but that doesn't seem efficient.\n\nWhat is the recommended approach to solve this problem?", "answer": "You can use `reflect` to convert the interface value back to the original `rsa.PublicKey` type. Here is an example code snippet:\n\n```go\nrsaKey := reflect.ValueOf(sshKey).\n    Convert(reflect.TypeOf(&rsa.PublicKey{})).Interface().(*rsa.PublicKey)\n```\n\nYou can try running this code in the Go Playground with a similar example: [link](http://play.golang.org/p/bcYhYHrIl_)."}
