{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_497487", "question": "John buys a box of 40 light bulbs.  He uses x of them and then gives half of what is left to a friend.  How many does he have left?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 12, what is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "John buys a box of 40 light bulbs.\nHe uses x of them, so he has 40 - x light bulbs left.\nHe gives half of what is left to a friend, which means he gives (40 - x) / 2 light bulbs to his friend.\nThe number of light bulbs he has left is (40 - x) - (40 - x) / 2.\nWe are given that the number of light bulbs he has left is 12, so we can write: (40 - x) - (40 - x) / 2 = 12.\nSimplifying the equation, we get: 2(40 - x) - (40 - x) = 24.\nExpanding and simplifying further, we get: 80 - 2x - 40 + x = 24.\nCombining like terms, we get: 40 - x = 24.\nSolving for x, we get: x = 16.\nThe value of x is 16.\n#### 16\nThe answer is: 16"}
