{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_498096", "question": "Tom can type x words a minute.  A page is 450 words. It would take him 50 to type out 10 pages. What is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the number of words Tom can type per minute.\nWe know that a page is 450 words. Therefore, Tom can type 10 pages, which is 10 * 450 = 4500 words.\nIt would take him 50 minutes to type out 10 pages.\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\nNumber of words Tom can type per minute * Number of minutes = Total number of words typed\nx * 50 = 4500\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\n50x = 4500\nTo isolate x, we divide both sides of the equation by 50:\n50x / 50 = 4500 / 50\nx = 90\nThe value of x is 90.\n#### 90\nThe answer is: 90"}
