 * (Percentage of carbohydrates in the snack/100)\n(Fat content in grams) = (Total weight of snack in grams) * (Percentage of fat in the snack/100)\n(Fiber content in grams) = (Total weight of snack in grams) * (Percentage of fiber in the snack/100)\n(Total calorie count) = [(Protein content in grams) * 4] + [(Carbohydrate content in grams) * 4] + [(Fat content in grams) * 9] + [(Fiber content in grams) * 2]\n\nIndividuals can then input their own values for the weight and nutrient percentages of the snack to calculate the total calorie count based on their specific dietary needs."}
