{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_600118", "question": "What do I do when I can't control my anger?\nHow do I control my anger and have patience?\n\nMulti-choice problem: Are these two questions inquiring about the same information?\nOPTIONS:\n[A]. no.\n[B]. yes.", "answer": "When you can't control your anger, imagine you have a balloon inside of you that fills up with air when you get angry. To control your anger and have patience, try to let some air out of the balloon slowly so it doesn't burst. You can do this by:\n\n1. Taking deep breaths: Breathe in through your nose, and out through your mouth like you're blowing out birthday candles.\n2. Count to 10: This helps your brain take a break from the angry feelings and think about something else.\n3. Talk to someone: Tell an adult, like a parent or a teacher, how you're feeling and why you're angry. They can help you understand and maybe find a way to fix the problem.\n4. Do something you enjoy: Draw, play with toys, or listen to music. Doing something fun can make you feel happier and less angry.\n5. Think about happy things: Close your eyes and picture a place or memory that makes you happy and safe. This can help make your anger go away.\n\nSo, for your multi-choice problem:\nThe answer is [B]. yes. Both questions are inquiring about the same information: how to control anger and have patience."}
