{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_319580", "question": "How can I create a function in C# that calculates the sum of an array of numbers?", "answer": "You can create a function in C# that calculates the sum of an array of numbers using the following code:\n\n```csharp\nint SumArray(int[] array)\n{ \n  int sum = 0; \n  foreach (int number in array) \n  { \n    sum += number; \n  } \n\n  return sum; \n}\n```\n\nIn this code, we define a function called `SumArray` that takes an integer array as an input parameter. Inside the function, we initialize a variable `sum` to 0. Then, we use a `foreach` loop to iterate through each element `number` in the input array. For each iteration, we add the current number to the `sum`. Finally, we return the calculated `sum` as the result of the function.\n\nYou can call this function by passing an integer array as an argument, and it will calculate and return the sum of all the numbers in the array."}
