{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_307123", "question": "How can I create a SQL query to retrieve the author name and the title of books containing the words \"data\" or \"Data\" from the books table?", "answer": "You can use the following SQL query to achieve that:\n\n```sql\nSELECT authors.name, books.title\n  FROM authors\n    INNER JOIN books ON authors.id = books.author_id\n  WHERE books.title LIKE '%data%'\n    OR books.title LIKE '%Data%';\n```\n\nThis query uses the `SELECT` statement to specify the columns we want to retrieve: `authors.name` and `books.title`. The `FROM` clause is used to specify the tables involved in the query, in this case, `authors` and `books`. The `INNER JOIN` keyword is used to join the tables based on their related columns, which in this case is `authors.id` and `books.author_id`.\n\nThe `WHERE` clause is used to filter the results based on the specified conditions. In this query, we use the `LIKE` operator combined with the `%` wildcard to match any book title that contains the word \"data\" or \"Data\". The `%` wildcard represents any number of characters, so `%data%` matches any string that has \"data\" anywhere within it.\n\nBy executing this SQL query, you will retrieve the author name and the title of books that include the words \"data\" or \"Data\" from the books table."}
