{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_672808", "question": "Answer this question.\n\n'Broadcast Yourself' is the slogan of which internet site?", "answer": "\"Broadcast Yourself\" is the slogan of the internet site called YouTube. YouTube is a massively popular video-sharing platform that allows users to upload, view, rate, share, comment on, and subscribe to other users' videos, as well as create playlists. It was created by three former PayPal employees, Chad Hurley, Steve Chen, and Jawed Karim, in February 2005 and later acquired by Google in November 2006 for $1.65 billion in stock.\n\nThe slogan \"Broadcast Yourself\" represents the core idea behind YouTube - empowering individual users to create, share, and broadcast their content to a global audience, without the need for traditional gatekeepers like television networks or film studios. This democratization of media production and distribution has fueled YouTube's rapid growth and made it one of the most visited websites in the world.\n\nOver the years, YouTube has undergone several transformations and added various features to improve users' experience and cater to their ever-evolving needs. Some of these features include:\n\n1. High Definition (HD) videos: YouTube initially supported low-resolution videos, but it eventually started offering HD videos with 720p, 1080p, 4K, and even 8K quality.\n\n2. YouTube Partner Program: Launched in 2007, this program allows content creators to monetize their videos through advertisements, subscriptions, and merchandise sales, enabling many creators to earn a living through their channels.\n\n3. YouTube Live: Introduced in 2011, this feature allows users to live stream events, conversations, and performances, fostering real-time engagement with viewers.\n\n4. YouTube Kids: Launched in 2015, YouTube Kids is a separate and family-friendly app that offers age-appropriate content for children and includes parental controls.\n\n5. YouTube Premium: This subscription-based service, formerly known as YouTube Red, offers ad-free access to all content on the platform, as well as access to exclusive, original series and movies produced by YouTube.\n\n6. YouTube Music: Originally a standalone app called \"YouTube Music Key,\" it has since been revamped and integrated with Google Play Music, providing users with access to a vast library of songs, albums, and music videos.\n\n7. Creator tools and resources: YouTube offers various editing tools, copyright management systems, and video analytics to help creators understand their audience and optimize their content strategy.\n\nThese features, along with many others, have kept YouTube at the forefront of online video sharing and streaming services. Today, YouTube hosts a diverse range of content, including music videos, vlogs, educational resources, gaming streams, and more, reflecting the tastes and interests of its global user base. As a result, YouTube has become a key platform for content creators, advertisers, and viewers alike, fostering a unique ecosystem that continues to shape the online video landscape."}
