st Center) and Los Angeles (at CBS Television City and the CBS Studio Center).  - Worst Week is an American sitcom which originally aired on CBS from September 22, 2008 to June 6, 2009. The series was based on the British sitcom \"The Worst Week of My Life\". The show was adapted for American audiences by Fox under the title \"Worst Week of My Life\", but a series failed to materialize after the pilot was filmed.  - Childrens Hospital (originally titled Children's Hospital as webisodes) is a satirical American comedy television series and web series that parodies the medical drama genre, created by and starring actor/comedian Rob Corddry. The series began on the web on TheWB.com with ten episodes, roughly five minutes in length, all of which premiered on December 8, 2008. Adult Swim picked up the rights to the show in 2009 and began airing episodes in 2010.  - Cartoon Network is an American basic cable and satellite television channel that operates daily from 6:00 AM to 8:00 PM (ET/PT) and is owned by Time Warner through the Turner Broadcasting System subsidiary. It was launched on October 1, 1992.   - A medical drama is a television program in which events center upon a hospital, an ambulance staff, or any medical environment and most medical episodes are one hour long and set in a hospital. Most current medical dramatic programming go beyond the events pertaining to the characters' jobs and portray some aspects of their personal lives. A typical medical drama might have a storyline in which two doctors fall in love. Communications theorist Marshall McLuhan, in his on the nature of media, predicted success for this particular genre on TV because the medium \"creates an obsession with bodily welfare\".   - Toonami is a brand name geared towards action-oriented programming, primarily consisting of American animation and Japanese anime. Originally an afternoon and evening block on Cartoon Network and ended on September 20, 2008, it is now (as of May 18, 2012) a late Saturday night adult-orientated animation block on Adult Swim. The brand was created by Sean Akins and Jason DeMarco and produced by Williams Street. The name is a portmanteau of the words \"cartoon\" and \"tsunami\", suggesting a \"tidal wave\" of animated shows.  - The Worst Week of My Life is a British television sitcom, first broadcast on BBC One between March and April 2004. A second series was aired between November and December 2005 and a three-part Christmas special, \"The Worst Christmas of My Life\" was shown during December 2006. It was written by Mark Bussell and Justin Sbresni.  - A web series is a series of scripted or non-scripted videos, generally in episodic form, released on the Internet and part of the web television medium, which first emerged in the late 1990s and become more prominent in the early 2000s (decade). A single instance of a web series program can be called an episode or \"webisode\", however the latter term is not often used. In general, web series can be watched on a range of platforms, including desktop, laptop, tablets and smartphones. They can also be watched on television.   - Robert William \"Rob\" Corddry (born February 4, 1971) is an American actor and comedian. He is known for his work as a correspondent on \"The Daily Show with Jon Stewart\" (20022006) and for his starring role in the comedy film \"Hot Tub Time Machine\" (2010). He is also the creator and star of the Adult Swim comedy series \"Childrens Hospital\" and won his first and second Emmy Awards in September 2012 and September 2013. Corddry currently co-stars in the HBO series \"Ballers\".  - Erinn Hayes ( née Carter ; born May 25 , 1976 ) is an American actress . She is known for her role as Dr. Lola Spratt on the Adult Swim comedy Childrens Hospital . She has played roles in a number of network sitcoms , including Alison on The Winner ( 2007 ) , Melanie Clayton on Worst Week ( 2008 -- 2009 ) , and Sheila on Guys with Kids ( 2012 -- 2013 ) . In 2012 , she had her 