n, and then increment the SI and DI pointers accordingly. After copying a row, we decrement the CL register and check if it's non-zero. If it is, we jump back to the COPY_BOX label to copy the next row. Once we have copied all 8 rows, we decrement the CH register and check if it's non-zero. If it is, we jump back to the INIT label to copy the next set of 8 rows.\n\nThis updated code ensures that the square is copied correctly to the desired coordinates (150,60)."}
