{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_27691", "question": "If a car rental company has 100 cars, and on average 80% of them are rented out each day, how many days will it take for the company to rent out 1,000 cars?", "answer": "To determine how many days it would take for the company to rent out 1,000 cars, we first need to find out how many cars are rented out per day. We know that 80% of the 100 cars are rented out daily:\n\nCars rented per day = Total cars * Percentage rented\n                    = 100 cars * 0.8\n                    = 80 cars\n\nNow, we want to find out how many days it takes to reach 1,000 rentals. To do this, we can divide the total number of rentals needed by the number of cars rented per day:\n\nDays to reach 1,000 rentals = Total rentals / Cars rented per day\n                            = 1,000 rentals / 80 cars per day\n                            = 12.5 days\n\nSince we cannot have half a day, we round up to the nearest whole number:\n\n13 days\n\nSo, it will take approximately 13 days for the car rental company to rent out 1,000 cars."}
