{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_901419", "question": "question: If, when the two parties of knights encounter one another after a month, exactly one knight changes from one travelling party to the other travelling party, that knight must be\nOptions:\n(A) P\n(B) Q\n(C) R\n(D) S\n(E) T\nanswer: Stream of consciousness: Q because Q always have to travel in northern route The answer is (B).\n\n\nq: List K consists of 10 consecutive integers. If -4 is the least integer in list K, what is the range of the positive integers in list K?\nOptions:\n(A) 5\n(B) 6\n(C) 7\n(D) 11\n(E) 4\na: Stream of consciousness: Answer = E = 4\nIf least = -4, then largest = 5\nRange = 5 - 1 = 4 The answer is (E).\n\n\nquestion: a piece of ribbon 4 yard long is used to make bows requiring 15 inches of ribbon for each.What is the maximum number of bows that can be made.\nOptions:\n(A) 9\n(B) 8\n(C) 7\n(D) 6\n(E) 5\nanswer: Stream of consciousness: 1 yard = 36 Inch\n4 yard = 36*4 = 144 inch\n15 inch req. for 1 bow\nMax. no. of bows possible = 144/15 = 9 bows and 9 inch ribbon left. The answer is (A).\n\n\nq: Find the value of y from (12)^3 x 6^4÷432 = y?\nOptions:\n(A) 5618\n(B) 5232\n(C) 5889\n(D) 5184\n(E) 5132\na: Stream of consciousness: Given Exp. = (12)3 x 64 = (12)3 x 64 = (12)2 x 62 = (72)2 = 5184\n432 12 x 62 The answer is (D).\n\n\nquestion: The smallest prime number is:\nOptions:\n(A) 1\n(B) 2\n(C) 3\n(D) 4\n(E) 5\nanswer: Stream of consciousness: The smallest prime number is 2. The answer is (B).\n\n\nquestion: If 10 litres of an oil of Rs.54 per litres be mixed with 5 litres of another oil of Rs.66 per litre then what is the rate of mixed oil per litre?\nOptions:\n(A) Rs.49.17\n(B) Rs.58\n(C) Rs.54.17\n(D) Rs.55.33\n(E) None of the above\nanswer:", "answer": "Stream of consciousness: First, find the total cost of both oils. \n10 litres * Rs.54 = Rs.540\n5 litres * Rs.66 = Rs.330\nTotal cost = Rs.540 + Rs.330 = Rs.870\n\nNow, find the total volume of the mixture.\n10 litres + 5 litres = 15 litres\n\nFinally, find the rate of mixed oil per litre.\nRs.870 ÷ 15 litres = Rs.58\n\nThe answer is (B) Rs.58."}
