{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_279303", "question": "How can I create a Node.JS web server for a movie database website that returns a JSON with a list of movies?", "answer": "You can use the Node.js framework Express to create a web server for your movie database website. Here's an example code that demonstrates how to achieve it:\n\n```javascript\nconst express = require('express');\nconst app = express();\nconst port = 8000;\n\nconst movies = [\n {\n name: 'Iron Man',\n genre: 'Action',\n rating: 8\n }\n];\n\napp.get('/movies', (req, res) => {\n res.json(movies);\n});\n\napp.listen(port, () => {\n console.log(`Server is running on port ${port}`);\n});\n```\n\nIn this code, we first import the `express` module and create an instance of the `express` object named `app`. We then define the `port` variable to specify the port number on which the server will run (in this example, it's set to 8000).\n\nNext, we create an array `movies` which holds the movie data. You can add more movies to this array as needed, following the same structure.\n\nThe `app.get('/movies', ...)` function sets up a route for the '/movies' endpoint. When a GET request is made to this endpoint, the server responds with the `movies` array in JSON format using the `res.json()` method.\n\nLastly, we call the `app.listen()` function to start the server on the specified port. The server will then log a message confirming that it's running.\n\nBy running this code, you can create a movie database web server that returns a JSON with a list of movies when accessed at the '/movies' endpoint."}
