{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_230550", "question": "How can I use Python's unit test mock to get the input arguments of a mocked function in order to assert that a variable, in this case `action`, within a function is getting set to its expected value? I am trying to mock `lib.event.Event`, but I'm having difficulty understanding how mock works from the documentation.", "answer": "Yes, you can indeed use Python's unittest.mock to achieve what you're trying to do. The unittest.mock module provides a `Mock` class which allows you to replace parts of your system under test and make assertions about how they have been used. In your case, you want to replace `lib.event.Event` with a `Mock` and then make assertions on it.\n\nHere is a step-by-step solution:\n\nStep 1: Import the necessary modules:\n```python\nfrom unittest.mock import patch, call\nimport unittest\nimport lib\n```\nStep 2: Create a class `Monolith` and its method `foo` that you want to test:\n```python\nclass Monolith(object):\n    def foo(self, raw_event):\n        action =  # ... Parse Event\n        # Middle of function\n        lib.event.Event(METADATA, action)\n        # Continue on to use the build event.\n```\nStep 3: Create the test case:\n```python\nclass TestMonolith(unittest.TestCase):\n    @patch('lib.event.Event')\n    def test_foo(self, mock_event):\n        # Instantiate Monolith class\n        m = Monolith()\n        # Call the method\n        m.foo('some raw event')\n        # Check if lib.event.Event is called with expected arguments\n        mock_event.assert_called_with(METADATA, 'expected action')\n```\nIn the test case, `@patch('lib.event.Event')` replaces `lib.event.Event` with a `Mock`. The `Mock` is then passed into the test case as `mock_event`. After calling the method `foo` on your `Monolith` instance, `lib.event.Event` would have been called with some arguments. You can then use `mock_event.assert_called_with()` to check if `lib.event.Event` was called with the expected arguments.\n\nStep 4: Run the test:\n```python\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    unittest.main()\n```\nThe test will pass if `lib.event.Event` was called with the expected arguments, and it will fail otherwise.\n\nRemember to replace `METADATA` and `'expected action'` with the actual expected values."}
