{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_447115", "question": "If Camila has gone hiking only 7 times in her life and Amanda has gone on 8 times as many hikes as Camila, and Steven has gone on 15 more hikes than Amanda, how many weeks would it take for Camila to reach the same number of hikes as Steven if she plans to go on 4 hikes per week?", "answer": "If Camila has gone hiking only 7 times in her life, and Amanda has gone on 8 times as many hikes as Camila, then Amanda has gone on 7 x 8 = 56 hikes.\nIf Steven has gone on 15 more hikes than Amanda, then Steven has gone on 56 + 15 = 71 hikes.\nIf Camila plans to go on 4 hikes per week, then we can calculate the number of weeks it would take for her to reach the same number of hikes as Steven. \nThe difference between Camila's current number of hikes (7) and Steven's number of hikes (71) is 71 - 7 = 64 hikes.\nTo reach the same number of hikes as Steven, Camila would need to go on an additional 64 hikes.\nIf Camila plans to go on 4 hikes per week, then it would take her 64 / 4 = 16 weeks to reach the same number of hikes as Steven.\n#### 16\nThe answer is: 16"}
