{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_985", "question": "Create a Python script that implements the quicksort algorithm for sorting a list of integers.\nPLAINFORMAT", "answer": "def quicksort(arr):\n    # Base case: if the array has 1 or 0 elements, it's already sorted\n    if len(arr) <= 1:\n        return arr\n\n    # Choose a pivot element from the middle of the array\n    pivot = arr[len(arr) // 2]\n\n    # Partition the array into three parts: left (elements less than pivot),\n    # middle (elements equal to pivot), and right (elements greater than pivot)\n    left = [x for x in arr if x < pivot]\n    middle = [x for x in arr if x == pivot]\n    right = [x for x in arr if x > pivot]\n\n    # Recursively sort the left and right partitions, then concatenate them with the middle partition\n    return quicksort(left) + middle + quicksort(right)\n\nprint(quicksort([3,6,8,10,1,2,1]))"}
