{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_884879", "question": "Q: Is the following a factual statement?\n\"An Asteroid can cause great damage if it lands on Earth.\"\nOptions:\n- yes\n- no\nChain-of-thought:", "answer": "1. An asteroid is a small, rocky object that orbits the Sun.\n2. Asteroids can range in size from tiny pebbles to large objects, hundreds of kilometers in diameter.\n3. If an asteroid enters Earth's atmosphere, it can either burn up, break apart, or reach the surface.\n4. The impact of an asteroid reaching Earth's surface depends on its size, composition, and speed.\n5. Large asteroid impacts have been linked to significant events in Earth's history, such as mass extinctions and climate change.\n6. Smaller impacts can still cause localized damage, such as the Tunguska event in 1908, which flattened trees over an area of 2,000 square kilometers.\n\nConclusion: Yes, the statement \"An asteroid can cause great damage if it lands on Earth\" is factual. The damage depends on the size, composition, and speed of the asteroid, but historically large impacts have had significant consequences on Earth's environment and life."}
