{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_479968", "question": "Miriam spent 30 minutes doing laundry, 15 minutes cleaning the bathroom, a certain amount of time cleaning her room, and 40 minutes doing homework. If she spent a total of two hours on these tasks, how long, in minutes, did she spend cleaning her room?", "answer": "Miriam spent 30 + 15 + x + 40 = 2 hours on these tasks.\nSince there are 60 minutes in an hour, 2 hours is equal to 2 x 60 = 120 minutes.\nSo, 30 + 15 + x + 40 = 120\nCombining like terms, 85 + x = 120\nSubtracting 85 from both sides, x = 120 - 85 = 35\nTherefore, Miriam spent 35 minutes cleaning her room.\n#### 35\nThe answer is: 35"}
