{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_461322", "question": "If Carla puts 79 apples in her backpack every morning for lunch and had 8 apples left at lunchtime after some were stolen by Buffy on the school bus and 26 fell out of a hole, how many apples did Buffy steal from Carla?", "answer": "Carla puts 79 apples in her backpack every morning.\nAfter some were stolen by Buffy and some fell out of a hole, Carla had 8 apples left at lunchtime.\nIf we subtract the 8 apples Carla had left from the 79 apples she put in her backpack, we get 79 - 8 = 71 apples.\nSince 26 apples fell out of a hole, we subtract 26 from the 71 apples to find out how many apples Buffy stole.\nTherefore, Buffy stole 71 - 26 = 45 apples.\n#### 45\nThe answer is: 45"}
