{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_350023", "question": "I have a table in PostgreSQL with a column defined as `timestamp with time zone`. The table is mapped to a struct in my Rust code. However, when I try to compile the code with the table's `DateTime` field set to `DateTime<Local>`, I get an error. Here is my code:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Serialize, Queryable)]\npub struct Location {\n    pub publication_time: DateTime<Local>,\n    pub id: i32,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub latitude: BigDecimal,\n    pub longitude: BigDecimal,\n}\n\ntable! {\n    locations {\n        publication_time -> Timestamptz,\n        id -> Integer,\n        name -> Text,\n        latitude -> Numeric,\n        longitude -> Numeric,\n    }\n}\n\nfn get_all_locations(pool: web::Data<Pool>) -> Result<Vec<Location>, diesel::result::Error> {\n    let conn = pool.get().unwrap();\n    let items = locations.load::<Location>(&conn)?;\n    Ok(items)\n}\n```\n\nAnd I receive the following error message:\n\n```\nerror[E0277]: the trait bound `DateTime<Local>: FromSql<diesel::sql_types::Timestamptz, Pg>` is not satisfied\n  --> src/controller.rs:21:27\n   |\n21 |     let items = locations.load::<Location>(&conn)?;\n   |                           ^^^^ the trait `FromSql<diesel::sql_types::Timestamptz, Pg>` is not implemented for `DateTime<Local>`\n   |\n   = help: the following implementations were found:\n             <DateTime<Utc> as FromSql<diesel::sql_types::Timestamptz, Pg>>\n   = note: required because of the requirements on the impl of `diesel::Queryable<diesel::sql_types::Timestamptz, Pg>` for `DateTime<Local>`\n   = note: 2 redundant requirements hidden\n   = note: required because of the requirements on the impl of `diesel::Queryable<(diesel::sql_types::Timestamptz, diesel::sql_types::Integer, diesel::sql_types::Text, diesel::sql_types::Numeric, diesel::sql_types::Numeric), Pg>` for `models::Location`\n   = note: required because of the requirements on the impl of `LoadQuery<_, models::Location>` for `locations::table`\n```\n\nI also have another program that inserts data into this table, and it works fine. The only difference is that the struct is annotated with `#[derive(Deserialize, Insertable)]`. Can someone explain why I'm getting this error and how to resolve it?", "answer": "Mapping a `Timestamptz` field to a `DateTime<Local>` is not directly supported by Diesel. It only provides the corresponding implementation for `DateTime<Utc>`. However, you can work around this limitation by using the `#[diesel(deserialize_as = \"...\")]` attribute on the `publication_time` field of your `Location` struct and providing a custom deserialization wrapper.\n\nHere is the updated code:\n\n```rust\n#[derive(Serialize, Queryable)]\npub struct Location {\n    #[diesel(deserialize_as = \"MyDateTimeWrapper\")]\n    pub publication_time: DateTime<Local>,\n    pub id: i32,\n    pub name: String,\n    pub latitude: BigDecimal,\n    pub longitude: BigDecimal,\n}\n\npub struct MyDatetimeWrapper(DateTime<Local>);\n\nimpl Into<DateTime<Local>> for MyDatetimeWrapper {\n    fn into(self) -> DateTime<Local> {\n        self.0\n    }\n}\n\nimpl<DB, ST> Queryable<ST, DB> for MyDateTimeWrapper\nwhere\n    DB: Backend,\n    DateTime<Utc>: Queryable<ST, DB>,\n{\n    type Row = <DateTime<Utc> as Queryable<ST, DB>>::Row;\n\n    fn build(row: Self::Row) -> Self {\n        Self(DateTime::<Utc>::build(row).with_timezone(&Local))\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIn this code, we define a custom wrapper struct called `MyDateTimeWrapper`, which holds a `DateTime<Local>`. We implement the `Into<DateTime<Local>>` trait for this wrapper so that it can be converted into a `DateTime<Local>`. Additionally, we implement the `Queryable` trait for `MyDateTimeWrapper`, using the implementation of `Queryable<ST, DB>` for `DateTime<Utc>`. This allows us to build a `MyDateTimeWrapper` from the database row and convert it to a `DateTime<Local>`.\n\nBy using this custom deserialization wrapper, you can now query the database and deserialize the `Timestamptz` field as a `DateTime<Local>`."}
