{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_464076", "question": "During the family reunion, Orlando gained 5 pounds, Jose gained two pounds more than twice what Orlando gained, and Fernando gained 3 pounds less than half of what Jose gained. What is the total weight, in pounds, that the three family members gained at their reunion?", "answer": "Orlando gained 5 pounds.\nTwice what Orlando gained is 2 * 5 = 10 pounds.\nJose gained 2 pounds more than twice what Orlando gained, so Jose gained 10 + 2 = 12 pounds.\nHalf of what Jose gained is 12 / 2 = 6 pounds.\nFernando gained 3 pounds less than half of what Jose gained, so Fernando gained 6 - 3 = 3 pounds.\nThe total weight that the three family members gained is 5 + 12 + 3 = 20 pounds.\n#### 20\nThe answer is: 20"}
