{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_514282", "question": "Please answer the following question: Write a multi-choice question for the following article: Article: A taxi hit a truck. A policeman spoke to the taxi driver and to the truck driver. He also spoke to Tom. He was a witness . This is what they said. TRUCK DRIVER: I was driving from the airport to Newton. A car crossed the road, so I slowed down. I did not stop. A taxi hit the back of my truck. Nobody was badly hurt but both cars were damaged. TAXI DRIVER: I was driving behind a truck a few kilometers from Newton. The truck stopped suddenly. The driver did not give me a warning. I was driving very slowly. I could not pass the truck because there were two cars coming near from Newton. My taxi hit the truck, and some glass cut my left hand. TOM: I was watching the traffic about a kilometer from the airport. A truck was going to Newton. It was not going very quickly. There was a taxi about two hundred meters behind the truck. It was going fast. When the truck slowed down, the taxi hit it. The taxi driver was not looking at the truck. He was looking out of the window at something. My friend saw the accident, too. Tom's friend spoke to the policeman and agreed with Tom.\nAnswer:", "answer": "Question: Based on the statements provided, which of the following best describes the reason behind the collision between the taxi and the truck?\n\nA. The truck driver stopped suddenly without giving the taxi driver a warning.\nB. The taxi driver was driving slowly and could not pass the truck due to oncoming traffic.\nC. The taxi driver was driving fast and looking out of the window when the truck slowed down.\nD. Both the taxi and the truck drivers were driving too fast.\n\nStep 1: Analyze the statements given by each individual\n- Truck driver: Slowed down but did not stop. Taxi hit the back of the truck.\n- Taxi driver: Truck stopped suddenly with no warning. Taxi driver couldn't pass the truck because of oncoming cars.\n- Tom: Taxi was going fast and the taxi driver was looking out of the window when the truck slowed down.\n\nStep 2: Determine the consistencies and inconsistencies between the statements\n- Consistencies: Both the truck driver and Tom stated that the truck slowed down.\n- Inconsistencies: Taxi driver claimed that he was driving slowly, while Tom stated that the taxi was going fast. Taxi driver stated that the truck stopped suddenly, while the truck driver and Tom only mentioned that the truck slowed down.\n\nStep 3: from all the statements, Tom and the truck driver's statements seem to be consistent regarding the truck slowing down and the taxi hitting it. \n\nFinal Answer: Based on the gathered information, the best description for the reason behind the collision is option C, \"The taxi driver was driving fast and looking out of the window when the truck slowed down.\""}
