{"id": "general_openhermes_2_5_2300_752230", "question": "Math problem: Solve -346388 - 492372 - 291000 = -3199*t - 9081*t for t.\nWhat is the solution?", "answer": "Hello, little buddy! Let's solve this math problem step by step. First, let's add the numbers on the left side of the equation:\n\n-346388 - 492372 - 291000\n\nWhen we add them together, we get:\n\n-1,129,760\n\nSo now the equation looks like:\n\n-1,129,760 = -3199*t - 9081*t\n\nNow, we need to combine the t's on the right side of the equation:\n\n-3199*t + (-9081)*t = (-3199 - 9081)*t\n\nThis becomes:\n\n-12,280*t\n\nSo now the equation looks like this:\n\n-1,129,760 = -12,280*t\n\nTo find the value of t, we need to divide -1,129,760 by -12,280. When we do this, we get:\n\nt = 92\n\nSo, the solution is t = 92. Great job, little one!"}
