r total earning is $1200 + $4000 = $5200. Her monthly budget aside from the insurance is $5200 x 95 / 100 = $4940. Therefore, she allocated $5200 - $4940 = $260 on insurance.\nThe answer: 260\nReverse engineering the question: Kristy, a sales representative earns a basic salary of $7.50 per hour plus a 16% commission on everything she sells. This month, she worked for 160 hours and sold $25000 worth of items. Her monthly budget for food, clothing, rent, transportation, bills and savings is 95% of her total monthly earnings and the rest will be put towards insurance. How much did she allocate to insurance?\n\nMike printed before the break 600 pamphlets per hour * 9 hours = 5400 pamphlets. The working speed of Mike after the break was 600 pamphlets per hour / 3 = 200 pamphlets per hour. Mike printed after the break 200 pamphlets per hour * 2 hours = 400 pamphlets. Leo worked third of the time that Mike worked before the break, so he worked 9 hours / 3 = 3 hours. Leo worked twice as fast as Mike before his break 600 pamphlets per hour * 2 = 1200 pamphlets per hour. Leo printed 1200 pamphlets per hour * 3 hours = 3600 pamphlets. Combining the pamphlets of Leo and Mike 5400 + 400 + 3600 = 9400 pamphlets.\nThe answer: 9400\nReverse engineering the question:", "answer": "Mike is a printing press operator who can print 600 pamphlets per hour. He worked for 9 hours before taking a 1-hour break. After the break, his working speed was reduced to a third of his original speed and he worked for 2 more hours. Meanwhile, Leo, another operator, worked for a third of the time Mike worked before the break, but he worked at twice the speed of Mike's original speed. How many pamphlets did they print in total?"}
